/* ==========================================
   EMBEDDED CONTENT DATA
   ========================================== */
const contentData = {
    paragraph: [
`Food Adulteration

Food adulteration is a serious crime in our society. It means mixing harmful substances with food items to increase profit. Adulterated food causes severe health hazards including cancer, kidney failure, and liver damage. Common adulterants include harmful chemicals in fruits, chalk powder in flour, and artificial colors in sweets. The government has enacted strict laws, but enforcement remains weak. Public awareness is crucial. We must buy food from trusted sources and check quality before consumption. Collective effort from consumers, sellers, and the government can eliminate this menace. A healthy nation depends on pure food.`,

`Early Rising

Early rising is a good habit that leads to success in life. The morning air is fresh and free from pollution. An early riser gets enough time to plan the day and complete tasks efficiently. Nature looks beautiful in the morning. The soft light of dawn refreshes the mind and body. Students who wake up early can study with full concentration. Many great men like Benjamin Franklin and Nelson Mandela were early risers. This habit improves health, increases productivity, and brings mental peace. We should practice early rising for a better life.`,

`Price Hike

Price hike means the unusual increase in the prices of essential commodities. It is a major problem in Bangladesh. The causes include shortage of supply, hoarding by dishonest traders, inflation, and global economic crisis. The poor and middle-class people suffer the most. They cannot afford basic needs like food, medicine, and education. The government should monitor markets strictly, increase production, and control inflation. Public awareness and honest business practices can also help reduce price hikes. A stable economy ensures a better life for all citizens.`,

`A Wise Judge

Once a greedy man stole a farmer's hen. The farmer caught him and took him to the village judge. The judge was known for his wisdom and fairness. The thief denied the accusation. The judge asked the farmer to describe the hen. The farmer said it had a red comb and laid an egg daily. The judge then asked the thief to describe the hen. The thief gave a different description. The judge immediately declared the farmer the true owner. The thief was punished. This story teaches us that truth always prevails before a wise judge.`,

`Women Empowerment

Women empowerment means giving women equal rights and opportunities in all spheres of life. In the past, women were confined to household chores. Today, they are contributing to education, politics, business, and science. Empowered women can change society. They bring new perspectives and balanced development. However, in rural areas, women still face discrimination, early marriage, and limited access to education. The government and NGOs are working to ensure women's rights. We must support gender equality for a prosperous and progressive nation.`,

`Road Accident

Road accidents have become a daily occurrence in Bangladesh. Reckless driving, over-speeding, overloading, and violation of traffic rules are the main causes. Many drivers do not have valid licenses. Unfit vehicles and poor road conditions also contribute to accidents. Every year, thousands of people lose their lives. It creates unbearable suffering for families. Strict enforcement of traffic laws, public awareness campaigns, and proper training for drivers can reduce accidents. We all must follow road safety rules to protect ourselves and others.`,

`Dowry System

